Assignment 4: Azure Data Factory End-to-End Pipeline
Description:
This project demonstrates the implementation of an end-to-end data pipeline using Microsoft Azure services, specifically Azure Storage Account and Azure Data Factory (ADF). The workflow covers data ingestion from a Blob Storage source, transformation orchestration using ADF activities, and data delivery to a target location with metadata validation.

Project Workflow:

Created a Resource Group in Azure Portal to organize resources.
Set up a Storage Account and Blob Container to store the source CSV file.
Uploaded input dataset (CSV) into Azure Blob Storage.
Configured Azure Data Factory and explored its UI (Author, Monitor, Manage).
Created Linked Service to connect ADF with Azure Blob Storage.
Defined datasets for both source and destination.
Used Get Metadata activity to validate file properties.
Built a pipeline using Copy Data activity for data movement.
Executed and monitored the pipeline using Debug/Trigger.
Assigned appropriate IAM roles to ensure secure access between services.

Output:

Successful execution of the pipeline.
Data transferred from Blob Storage to destination.
Metadata validation completed successfully.
Screenshots and detailed explanation are included in the attached PDF file.
Conclusion

This assignment provides hands-on experience in building a real-world ETL pipeline using Azure services, focusing on data integration, workflow automation, and cloud resource management.
